[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pape Souare: Crystal Palace sign Senegal defender from Lille

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Crystal Palace say they have have completed the signing of full-back Pape Souare from Lille on a three-and-half-year deal for an undisclosed fee, subject to a work permit.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 24-year-old Lille academy product has five caps for Senegal and played at the Africa Cup of Nations last month.
Souare is manager Alan Pardew's third signing in a week after the arrivals of Jordon Mutch and Shola Amoebi.
Eagles chairman Steve Parish originally announced the deal on Friday.
He tweeted: "Delighted that Pape Souare has just this minute signed for Crystal Palace. A warm welcome from all of us."
